# POS Register — Full Logic Reference

Use this when changing POS register, cart, checkout, or related views/JS. Follow MVP: SQL in `models/pos/pos.php`, HTTP in `POSRegisterController`, display in views/JS.

**Related rules:** `pos-stock-availability.mdc` (warehouse stock edge cases), `exotic-india-integration.mdc` (RetailApiClient / vendor-api), **`pos-order-payment-invoice.mdc`** (order create, payments, invoices — full detail).

---

## Architecture

```
Browser (pos.js + pos_cart_hooks.js + index.php inline JS)
    ↓ same-origin AJAX
POSRegisterController (Presenter)
    ↓
models/pos/pos.php          → vp_products + vp_stock_movements (local catalog/stock)
integrations/exotic/      → https://www.exoticindia.com/api (cart, product, order)
helpers/pos_payment_receipt.php → pos_payments, receipts, invoice eligibility
views/pos_register/         → UI only
```

**Cart truth source:** Exotic retail API session cart (`/cart/retrieve`). POS does not maintain a local cart DB — it proxies via `cart-api`.

**Catalog truth source:** `vp_products` (local) enriched with Exotic `/product/code` for price, addons, GST display.

**Warehouse stock truth source:** Latest `vp_stock_movements.running_stock` per `product_id` + `warehouse_id` (see stock rule).

